radiographic_examinations.findings: Evidence of free air beneath the diaphragm seen on prior outside hospital chest radiograph was better appreciated on that study, but still seen in the partially imaged left upper abdomen. Reticular opacities at the lung bases, right greater than left may relate to chronic interstitial lung disease. There is blunting of the left costophrenic angle likely due to atelectasis, but underlying pleural effusion is not excluded.
